xternal accountability purposes. Keeping these results private helps prevent misuse or comparison among students, families, and communities.&#10;4. Publication of school development plans: Schools will publish self-evaluations and development plans annually to demonstrate their approach to educational improvements and child well-being. This process focuses on the school's performance as a whole rather than individual assessments.&#10;5. Teacher-parent conversations: Encouraging regular conversations between teachers and parents about a child's progress, strengths, and areas for improvement can help shift the focus from accountability to learning and development.">
