    <edge source="1. The new curriculum's implementation strategy involves cluster groups working with a smaller number of pioneer schools to create and test materials. These schools focus on examining the curriculum as a whole and considering its practical application in their specific context.&#10;2. Sixty applicants from 170 previous pioneer schools were chosen, with four per region, to serve as innovation schools. These schools have been tasked with examining the curriculum and producing reports on their reflections and findings.&#10;3. A research company named Wavehill compiled these reports into an overall report, highlighting themes emerging from headteachers' perspectives on implementing the curriculum in their schools.&#10;4. The current focus is on how individual schools can implement the curriculum in a practical manner, with cluster groups playing an essential role in this process. Regional consortia will provide differentiated professional learning support for schools at various stages of implementation, emphasizing peer-to-peer sharing and collaboration." target="1. Based on the transcript, there was not a clearly defined coordinated lobbying effort to present a particular view on modernizing Religious Education (RE). However, various groups and individuals with specific interests in RE did feel galvanized to respond to the White Paper on this issue.&#10;2. Politicians like Kirsty Williams AM will need to consider these responses when making decisions about the future of RE and Relationships and Sexuality Education (RSE) in the curriculum. They recognize the importance of preparing young people for a diverse society, as evidenced by positive feedback on the emphasis of ongoing assessment to support children's learning and progression regarding world views and world religions.&#10;3. The Welsh government is considering creating a directory of resources to implement the Welsh dimension in the new curriculum, which shows their commitment to ensuring that the new curriculum reflects diverse perspectives and prepares young people for living in a multicultural society.&#10;&#10;In summary, while there might not have been a coordinated lobbying effort, various groups and individuals presented their viewpoints on modernizing RE in Wales. Politicians like Kirsty Williams AM will need to consider these responses as they make decisions about the future of RE and RSE in the curriculum, ensuring that young people are prepared for life in a diverse society.">
