igel Newton's concern about disadvantaged students and pupils of lower attainment, Kirsty Williams AM asserts that she would not pursue any changes leading to segregation or increased inequality.&#10;5. She believes that the comments made by Welsh Local Government Association (WLGA) and Association of Directors of Education Wales are outdated, and progress has been made in addressing their concerns.&#10;6. When questioned about potential unintended consequences, Kirsty Williams AM expresses her intention to establish a clear distinction between assessment for learning and accountability within the new Welsh education system. This will help prevent negative unintended outcomes, such as those seen with BTEC science.">
