uring that the new curriculum reflects diverse perspectives and prepares young people for living in a multicultural society.&#10;&#10;In summary, while there might not have been a coordinated lobbying effort, various groups and individuals presented their viewpoints on modernizing RE in Wales. Politicians like Kirsty Williams AM will need to consider these responses as they make decisions about the future of RE and RSE in the curriculum, ensuring that young people are prepared for life in a diverse society.">
